messages.message:
This is for PreProd AI Hub Build. Two things:

1. I had an excel sheet with a large table, but it didnt recognize it as a table. When I corrected the field to "Table", it worked fine (which by the way is an enormous improvement!!). It is somehow unintuitive that AI Hub first tries to find a Single Field and gives a weird answer, and only corrects itself when you change to Table
2. For Output, we give the option to download as an excel or csv. Two things: it seems to store al the numbers as text strings. I pushes it out in an unintuitive format. I think it is fine for CSV, but for excel I'd have expected an ordinary vertical table.
Video here (https://www.loom.com/share/4a2a13918d254d0a97882c2e96392cf0?sid=8500bfb1-195e-47a5-a05f-eabdb0dadbf8), PW: 9krq9nuc

In Excel, I was able to use Textsplit, paste as values, and find replace of ", to get the data in a usable format :slightly_smiling_face: Good news is that the extraction was fully correct :slightly_smiling_face:
Let’s talk about the Export functionality tomorrow. I’m curious to hear more use cases.
